Then when creating the new UNI tunnel, set prvtMplsTunnelUNIDiversityTableIndex in the mplsTunnelTable to the list_index corresponding to the Diversity Table to be used. A diversity list is read-only if it is referenced by an active row in the mplsTunnelTable that is admin_status up. Under these circumstances, no individual rows/diversity requirements making up the list can be added, modified or deleted. A list of diversity requirements can only be satisfied by signaling if all of the referenced rows in the mplsTunnelTable are oper_status up when signaling is initiated. If the requirements cannot be satisfied, any tunnel attempting to use the list will remain oper_status down.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDiversityEntry.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDiversityEntry
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDiversityEntry.description: An entry in this table corresponds to an entry in the mplsTunnelTable. A subsequent Tunnel that references this entry will be created Diverse from the tunnel row entry specified here.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivListIdx.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivListIdx
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivListIdx.description: Primary index into this table identifying a particular list of Diversity requirements.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivIdx.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivIdx
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivIdx.description: Secondary index into this table identifying a Diversity requirement within the list.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRowPointer.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRowPointer
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRowPointer.description: This field represents a pointer to the entry in the mplsTunnelTable to which the Diversity requirement applies. The array of longs specified here is configured as the OID of the corresponding tunnel.

prvtMplsTunnelOperStatus.name: prvtMplsTunnelOperStatus
prvtMplsTunnelOperStatus.description: The Oper Status of the mplsTunnelTable row referred to by prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivPointer. If this tunnel is removed from the mplsTunnelTable then this is set to AMB_OPER_STATUS_DOWN. This field is used to determine whether a diversity requirement can currently be satisfied by signaling.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRowStatus.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRowStatus
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create or delete this row.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRequirement.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRequirement
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivRequirement.description: This field indicates the Diversity Requirement for the corresponding tunnel. Once an row entry has been created and is oper status 'up' for this tunnel this value cannot be altered.

prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivAccess.name: prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivAccess
prvtMplsTunnelUNIDivAccess.description: This field indicates the access (read-only or writable) that the user has over this row entry. The circumstances under which a row is read-only are described above.

prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnableTable.name: prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnableTable
prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnableTable.description: The prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnable Table allows a manager to enable or disable TRAPs.

prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnableEntry.name: prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnableEntry
prvtMplsTunnelTrapEnableEntry.description: An entry in this table is used to configure trap support for this instance of TE-MIB

mplsTunnelTrapEnable.name: mplsTunnelTrapEnable
mplsTunnelTrapEnable.description: If this object is true, then it enables the generation of mplsTunnelUp and mplsTunnelDown traps, otherwise these traps are not emitted.

mplsTunnelHoldTimer.name: mplsTunnelHoldTimer
mplsTunnelHoldTimer.description: Defines a period in seconds needed to wait before rebuilding backup or primary tunnels if a frr condition occurs Currently no more than 10 seconds are allowed

mplsTeMibEntityScalarTable.name: mplsTeMibEntityScalarTable
mplsTeMibEntityScalarTable.description: The mplsTeMibEntityScalarTable contains all MPLS Tunnel scalars.

mplsTeMibEntityScalarEntry.name: mplsTeMibEntityScalarEntry
mplsTeMibEntityScalarEntry.description: The mplsTeMibEntityScalarTable contains all MPLS Tunnel scalars.

mplsTunnelConfigured.name: mplsTunnelConfigured
mplsTunnelConfigured.description: The number of tunnels configured on this device. A tunnel is considered configured if the mplsTunnelRowStatus is active(1).

mplsTunnelActive.name: mplsTunnelActive
mplsTunnelActive.description: The number of tunnels active on this device. A tunnel is considered active if the mplsTunnelOperStatus is up(1).

mplsTunnelTEDistProto.name: mplsTunnelTEDistProto
mplsTunnelTEDistProto.description: The traffic engineering distribution protocol(s) used by this LSR. Note that an LSR may support more than one distribution protocol simultaneously.

mplsTunnelMaxHops.name: mplsTunnelMaxHops
mplsTunnelMaxHops.description: The maximum number of hops that can be specified for a tunnel on this device.

mplsTunnelNotificationMaxRate.name: mplsTunnelNotificationMaxRate
mplsTunnelNotificationMaxRate.description: This variable indicates the maximum number of notifications issued per second. If events occur more rapidly, the implementation may simply fail to emit these notifications during that period, or may queue them until an appropriate time. A value of 0 means no throttling is applied and events may be notified at the rate at which they occur.

mplsTunnelSonetResTable.name: mplsTunnelSonetResTable
mplsTunnelSonetResTable.description: The mplsTunnelSonetResTable allows a manager to specify which Sonet-specific resources are desired for an MPLS tunnel. Note that these attributes are in addition to those specified in mplsTunnelResourceTable. This table also allows several tunnels to point to a single entry in this table, implying that these tunnels should share resources.

mplsTunnelSonetResEntry.name: mplsTunnelSonetResEntry
mplsTunnelSonetResEntry.description: An entry in this table represents a set of Sonet resources for an MPLS tunnel. An entry can be created by a network administrator or by an SNMP agent as instructed by any MPLS signaling protocol.

mplsTunnelSonetResRCC.name: mplsTunnelSonetResRCC
mplsTunnelSonetResRCC.description: Requested Contiguous Concatenation. Indicates the types of contiguous concatenation requested for this LSP. This field is only valid if <lsp_encoding> is SDH or SONET, and the <resource_pointer> is 0.0.

mplsTunnelSonetResNCC.name: mplsTunnelSonetResNCC
mplsTunnelSonetResNCC.description: Requested Number of Contiguous Components. Indicates the number of identical SDH/SONET SPEs/VCs that are requested to be concatenated, as indicated in the <rcc> field. This field is only valid if <lsp_encoding> is SDH or SONET, and the <resource_pointer> is 0.0.

mplsTunnelSonetResNVC.name: mplsTunnelSonetResNVC
mplsTunnelSonetResNVC.description: This field indicates the number of signals that are requested to be virtually concatenated. These signals are all of the same type. This field is valid only if <lsp_encoding> is SDH or SONET, and the <resource_pointer> is 0.0.

mplsTunnelSonetResMultiplier.name: mplsTunnelSonetResMultiplier
mplsTunnelSonetResMultiplier.description: This field is a bit field indicating the number of identical signals that are requested for the LSP. This field is valid only if <lsp_encoding> is SDH or SONET, and the <resource_pointer> is 0.0.

mplsTunnelSonetResTransparency.name: mplsTunnelSonetResTransparency
mplsTunnelSonetResTransparency.description: This field is a bit field indicating the type of Transparency being requested. Several flags can be combined to provide different types of transparency. Not all combinations are necessarily valid. This field is valid only if <lsp_encoding> is SDH or SONET, and the <resource_pointer> is 0.0.

mplsTunnelSonetResRowStatus.name: mplsTunnelSonetResRowStatus
mplsTunnelSonetResRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, modify, and/or delete a row in this table.

mplsTunnelSonetResSignalType.name: mplsTunnelSonetResSignalType
mplsTunnelSonetResSignalType.description: Indicates the overhead termination type and is interpreted in relation to the LSP Encoding Type.

mplsTunnelErrorTable.name: mplsTunnelErrorTable
mplsTunnelErrorTable.reference: Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) Traffic Engineering (TE) Management Information Base (MIB), Srinivasan, C., Viswanathan, A., Nadeau, T., RFC 3812, June 2004.
mplsTunnelErrorTable.description: This table 'augments' the mplsTunnelTable. This table provides per-tunnel information about errors. Errors may be detected locally or reported through the signaling protocol. Error reporting is not exclusive to GMPLS and this table may be applied in MPLS systems.

mplsTunnelErrorEntry.name: mplsTunnelErrorEntry
mplsTunnelErrorEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the LSR for every tunnel where error information is visible to the LSR. Note that systems which read the objects in this table one at a time may experience a discontinuity as the result of a new error occurring in between object reads. Systems that are vulnerable to this should read mplsTunnelErrorLastTime before and after reading the other objects.

mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType.name: mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType
mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType.description: The nature of the last error. Provides interpretation context for mplsTunnelErrorProtocolCode and mplsTunnelErrorProtocolSubcode. A value of noError (0) shows that there is no error associated with this tunnel and means that the other objects in this table entry have no meaning. A value of unknown (1) shows that there is an error but that no additional information about the cause is known. The error may have been received in a signaled message or generated locally. A value of protocol (2) or pathComputation (3) indicates that the cause of an error and identifies an error that has been received through signaling or will itself be signaled. A value of localConfiguration (4), localResources (5) or localOther (6) identifies an error which has been detected by the local node, but which will not be reported through signaling.

mplsTunnelErrorLastTime.name: mplsTunnelErrorLastTime
mplsTunnelErrorLastTime.description: The time at which the last error occurred. This is presented as the value of SysUpTime when the error occurred or was reported to this node. If mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType has the value noError (0), then this object is ignored.

mplsTunnelErrorReporterType.name: mplsTunnelErrorReporterType
mplsTunnelErrorReporterType.description: The address type of the error reported. This object is used to aid in interpretation of mplsTunnelErrorReporter.

mplsTunnelErrorReporter.name: mplsTunnelErrorReporter
mplsTunnelErrorReporter.reference: RFC3291, Textual Conventions for Internet Network Addresses, Section 4. Usage Hints.
mplsTunnelErrorReporter.description: The address of the node reporting the last error, or the address of the resource (such as an interface) associated with the error. If mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType has the value noError (0), then this object is ignored. If mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType has the value unknown (1), localConfiguration (4), localResources (5), or localOther (6) this object MAY contain a zero value. This object should be interpreted in the context of the value of the object mplsTunnelErrorReporterType.

mplsTunnelErrorCode.name: mplsTunnelErrorCode
mplsTunnelErrorCode.reference: 1. Braden, R. (Ed.) et al., Resource ReserVation Protocol -- Version 1 Functional Specification, RFC 2205, September 1997. 2. RSVP-TE: Extensions to RSVP for LSP Tunnels, Awduche et al., RFC 3209, December 2001. 3. Generalized MPLS Signaling - RSVP-TE Extensions, Berger, L. (Editor), RFC 3473, January 2003.
mplsTunnelErrorCode.description: The primary error code associated with the last error. The interpretation of this error code depends on the value of mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType. If the value of mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType is noError (0) the value of this object should be 0 and should be ignored. If the value of mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType is protocol (2) the error should be interpreted in the context of the signling protocol identified by the mplsTunnelSignallingProto object. Values in excess 32767 of are not used by signaling protocols and may safely be used as implementation-specific error codes.

mplsTunnelErrorSubcode.name: mplsTunnelErrorSubcode
mplsTunnelErrorSubcode.reference: 1. Braden, R. (Ed.) et al., Resource ReserVation Protocol -- Version 1 Functional Specification, RFC 2205, September 1997. 2. RSVP-TE: Extensions to RSVP for LSP Tunnels, Awduche et al., RFC 3209, December 2001. 3. Generalized MPLS Signaling - RSVP-TE Extensions, Berger, L. (Editor), RFC 3473, January 2003.
mplsTunnelErrorSubcode.description: The secondary error code associated with the last error and the protocol used to signal this tunnel. This value is interpreted in the context of the value of mplsTunnelErrorCode. If the value of mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType is noError (0) the value of this object should be 0 and should be ignored.

mplsTunnelErrorTLVs.name: mplsTunnelErrorTLVs
mplsTunnelErrorTLVs.reference: Generalized MPLS Signaling - RSVP-TE Extensions, Berger, L. (Editor), RFC 3473, January 2003.
mplsTunnelErrorTLVs.description: The sequence of interface identifier TLVs reported with the error by the protocol code. The interpretation of the TLVs and the encoding within the protocol are described in the references. A value of zero in the first octet indicates that no TLVs are present.

mplsTunnelErrorHelpString.name: mplsTunnelErrorHelpString
mplsTunnelErrorHelpString.description: A textual string containing information about the last error, recovery actions and support advice. If there is no help string this object contains a zero length string. If the value of mplsTunnelErrorLastErrorType is noError (0) this object should contain a zero length string, but may contain a help string indicating that there is no error.

mplsTunnelUp.name: mplsTunnelUp
mplsTunnelUp.description: This notification is generated when a mplsTunnelOperStatus object for one of the configured tunnels is about to leave the down state and transition into some other state (but not into the notPresent state). This other state is indicated by the included value of mplsTunnelOperStatus. This structure is the same as the generic AMB_MPLS_TUNNEL_TRAP_COMMON.

mplsTunnelDown.name: mplsTunnelDown
mplsTunnelDown.description: This notification is generated when a mplsTunnelOperStatus object for one of the configured tunnels is about to enter the down state from some other state (but not from the notPresent state). This other state is indicated by the included value of mplsTunnelOperStatus. This structure is the same as the generic AMB_MPLS_TUNNEL_TRAP_COMMON.

mplsTunnelRerouted.name: mplsTunnelRerouted
mplsTunnelRerouted.description: This notification is generated when a tunnel is rerouted. If the actual path is used, then this object MAY contain the new path for this tunnel some time after this trap is issued by the agent. This structure is the same as the generic AMB_MPLS_TUNNEL_TRAP_COMMON.

mplsTunnelReoptimized.name: mplsTunnelReoptimized
mplsTunnelReoptimized.description: This notification is generated when a tunnel is reoptimized. If the mplsTunnelARHopTable is used, then this tunnel instance's entry in the mplsTunnelARHopTable MAY contain the new path for this tunnel some time after this trap is issued by the agent. This structure is the same as the generic AMB_MPLS_TUNNEL_TRAP_COMMON.

mplsTeModuleFullCompliance.name: mplsTeModuleFullCompliance
mplsTeModuleFullCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents that provide full support the MPLS-TE-STD-MIB module.

mplsTeModuleReadOnlyCompliance.name: mplsTeModuleReadOnlyCompliance
mplsTeModuleReadOnlyCompliance.description: Compliance requirement for implementations that only provide read-only support for MPLS-TE-STD-MIB. Such devices can then be monitored but cannot be configured using this MIB modules.

mplsTunnelGroup.name: mplsTunnelGroup
mplsTunnelGroup.description: Necessary, but not sufficient, set of objects to implement tunnels. In addition, depending on the type of the tunnels supported (for example, manually configured or signaled, persistent or non- persistent, etc.), the following other groups defined below are mandatory: mplsTunnelManualGroup and/or mplsTunnelSignaledGroup, mplsTunnelIsNotIntfcGroup and/or mplsTunnelIsIntfcGroup.

mplsTunnelManualGroup.name: mplsTunnelManualGroup
mplsTunnelManualGroup.description: Object(s) needed to implement manually configured tunnels.

mplsTunnelSignaledGroup.name: mplsTunnelSignaledGroup
mplsTunnelSignaledGroup.description: Objects needed to implement signaled tunnels.

mplsTunnelScalarGroup.name: mplsTunnelScalarGroup
mplsTunnelScalarGroup.description: Scalar object needed to implement MPLS tunnels.

mplsTunnelIsIntfcGroup.name: mplsTunnelIsIntfcGroup
mplsTunnelIsIntfcGroup.description: Objects needed to implement tunnels that are interfaces.

mplsTunnelIsNotIntfcGroup.name: mplsTunnelIsNotIntfcGroup
mplsTunnelIsNotIntfcGroup.description: Objects needed to implement tunnels that are not interfaces.

mplsTunnelCRLDPResOptionalGroup.name: mplsTunnelCRLDPResOptionalGroup
mplsTunnelCRLDPResOptionalGroup.description: Set of objects implemented for resources applicable for tunnels signaled using CR-LDP.

mplsTunnelSonetGroup.name: mplsTunnelSonetGroup
mplsTunnelSonetGroup.description: Set of objects needed to implement Sonet. None of these objects are mandatory.

mplsTunnelUniGroup.name: mplsTunnelUniGroup
mplsTunnelUniGroup.description: Set of objects needed to implement UNI. None of these objects are mandatory.

mplsTunnelBackupGroup.name: mplsTunnelBackupGroup
mplsTunnelBackupGroup.description: Set of objects needed for backup tunnels. None of these objects are mandatory.

mplsTunnelARHopGroup.name: mplsTunnelARHopGroup
mplsTunnelARHopGroup.description: Set of objects relating to ARHop. None of these objects are mandatory.

mplsTunnelCHopGroup.name: mplsTunnelCHopGroup
mplsTunnelCHopGroup.description: Set of objects relating to CHop. None of these objects are mandatory.

mplsDiffServGroup.name: mplsDiffServGroup
mplsDiffServGroup.description: Set of objects relating to DiffServ. None of these objects are mandatory.

mplsTeNotificationGroup.name: mplsTeNotificationGroup
mplsTeNotificationGroup.description: Set of notifications implemented in this module. None is mandatory.
